text.text:
Sri Rama temple, where lord Sri Ram was pleased by badri and granted his wish to stay on his head along with Sita, but he forgot to wear the shank and sudarsan in the correct hands.

You can keep your mobile/electronic devices and luggage safely in lockers near the temple. If it's not during kalyana mahotsavams near Sri Rama Navami, you can avail free darshan within 10 mins, else you can buy a ‚Çπ100/- tkt as well.

The temple has a museum where all historical things related to the temple, ramadasa and many other things are safely stored .

You can visit the place where badri's wish was granted by lord Rama after you darshan lord Rama from garbha gudi.

You can visit the coast of the Godavari river, you kalyana katta, lord Anjaneya temple and people also avail pinda karmas near the coast.

text.text: Lord Sree Sita Ramachandra Swamy Temple in Bhadrachalam is a Hindu temple of Lord Rama located in Telangana, India. The area is called as Bhadrachalam and is the venue of grand celebrations on Rama Navami day, when the wedding anniversary of Lord Rama and his consort Sita takes place with much fanfare, huge rush on Sunday

text.text: Temple dedicated to Lord Rama, Seetha, and Lakshmana on the banks of River Godavari. Bhadrachalam is approximately 112 km from Khammam and 188 km from Rajmendry (AP). Bhakt Ramdas has constructed the temple and composed many Kirtanas, which are known even today. The temple is located on a small hillock, and one has to climb 20 or 30 steps. Well maintained and clean temple. There are several small shrines and separate shrines for Goddess Mahalakshmi, Bhadradri, and Lord Hanuman. Temple also has a shrine for Ramdaa. The tradition followed at the temple is Vaishna Agama, similar to that of Sri Rangam. Sri Rams Navami, Mookoti Ekadasi and annual Bramotsavam are celebrated. One must visit this beautifulvt

text.text: The Sita Ramachandraswamy Temple at Bhadrachalam exudes spiritual serenity, with its intricate architecture and tranquil surroundings creating a perfect ambiance for devotion. The divine aura and the melodious hymns during prayer services contribute to a truly uplifting experience, making it a must-visit destination for seekers of spiritual solace.

text.text: Ramalayam is famous worship place,  a very peaceful atmosphere is present at ramalayam. There is uchitha darshanam(free darshanam) but queue is long it is based upon day . Sometimes it takes only 5 minutes but some times it takes 2-3 hours also. On regular days darshanam can be made fastly on special occasions it is a bit harder. Prasadam is made with fully hygiene environment. And it is available in the temple it self (at backside entrence). Best place to find peace in you.
